ğŸŸ¥ 1ï¸âƒ£ Brute Force (O(nÂ²)) âŒ

Idea
  Try every possible pair
  Mark used elements

âŒ Too slow for n = 10âµ


ğŸŸ¨ 2ï¸âƒ£ Better (Sorting + Two Pointers) âœ…
Idea
  Sort the array
  Use two pointers:
  l â†’ smallest
  r â†’ largest
  Compare nums[l] + nums[r] with k

class Solution {
public:
    int maxOperations(vector<int>& nums, int k) {
        sort(nums.begin(), nums.end());
        int l = 0, r = nums.size() - 1;
        int count = 0;

        while (l < r) {
            int sum = nums[l] + nums[r];

            if (sum == k) {
                count++;
                l++;
                r--;
            }
            else if (sum < k) {
                l++;
            }
            else {
                r--;
            }
        }
        return count;
    }
};

Complexity
Time: O(n log n)
Space: O(1)


ğŸŸ© 3ï¸âƒ£ OPTIMAL (Hash Map, O(n)) ğŸ”¥

ğŸ”‘ Core Idea
  For each number x, look for k - x
  If it exists â†’ form a pair
  Else â†’ store x for future

Optimal C++ Code
class Solution {
public:
    int maxOperations(vector<int>& nums, int k) {
        unordered_map<int, int> freq;
        int count = 0;

        for (int num : nums) {
            int need = k - num;

            if (freq[need] > 0) {
                count++;
                freq[need]--;
            } else {
                freq[num]++;
            }
        }
        return count;
    }
};

| Approach              | Time       | Space    |
| --------------------- | ---------- | -------- |
| Brute                 | O(nÂ²)      | O(1)     |
| Sort + 2P             | O(n log n) | O(1)     |
| **HashMap (Optimal)** | **O(n)**   | **O(n)** |

